parameters.description: A cursor for pagination. `starting_after` is an object ID that marks your position in the list. IsFeatured.description: Whether or not the plan is masked featured

IsEmailVerified.description: Indicates whether user's email is verified

Superiority.description: Superiority of the plan. Might be used to order the plans

Avatar.description: Avatar of the assistant. URL or base64 string

Language1.description: User's language preference. Should match locales[x].name of the /locale.json

Image.description: Image/icon for the preset. SVG source code or name of the any icon from Tabler Icons (example: access-point, leaf)

CreditCount.description: Value indicates the amount of the credit.

FeatureList.description: Comma separated list of the features

ExternalId.description: Id of the voice in the 3rd party service

Icon.description: Icon for the plan. SVG source code or name of the any icon from Tabler Icons (example: access-point, leaf)

Price.description: Money amount in currency minor. For example 1USD = 100, 1JPY = 1 etc.

fraction_digits.description: Fraction digits of the currency. For example, this value is 2 for USD, 0 JPY, 3 for BHD

PaymentGateway.description: Payment gateway used to create the order

has_password.description: Indicates whether user has a password defined. Users who signed up through the 3rd party login services such as Google or Github, may not have a password by defult.

avatar.description: URL of the user's avatar. Currently avatars are being provided by Gravatar.

workspaces.description: List of workspaces the user is a member of

owned_workspaces.description: List of workspaces the user owned

canceled_at.description: Date time when the subscription cancelled. Null if not cancelled yet.

cancel_at.description: Date time when the subscription is scheduled to cancel. Null if not scheduled.

is_eligible_for_trial.description: Whether or not the workspace is eligible for a free trial
